  "title": "Junior Content Developer (AMK) *3mth to 1 yr Contract",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Description</strong></h2><p>We are seeking a skilled Content Developer to join our team . The ideal candidate will have a strong background in creating high-quality content that engages and informs our target audience.<br /></p><h2><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li>Create, edit, and publish engaging content for various platforms, including websites, social media, and blogs.</li><li>Collaborate with marketing and design teams to develop content strategies that meet business goals.</li><li>Conduct research to ensure content accuracy and relevance to the target audience.</li><li>Optimize content for SEO to improve visibility and engagement.</li><li>Analyze content performance metrics and make data-driven recommendations for improvements.</li><li></li></ul><h2><strong>Skills and Qualifications</strong></h2><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Communications, Marketing, English, or a related field.</li><li>2-4 years of experience in content development or a similar role.</li><li>Strong writing and editing skills with a keen eye for detail.</li><li>Experience in e-learning development </li><li>Familiarity with SEO best practices and content management systems (CMS).</li><li>Proficiency in using social media platforms and understanding of their respective audiences.</li><li>Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>5 day week @ AMK (Travel to site at Changi area whenever required.</li><li>Singaporeans only.</li></ul><p>Maestro HR<br />damien lee tian hong<br />R1106726<br />16C8462</p>",
